model.metaheuristic.algorithm.singleobjective.geneticalgorithm

Class GeneticAlgorithm<S extends Solution<?>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.metaheuristic.algorithm.AbstractEvolutionaryAlgorithm<S>
      • model.metaheuristic.algorithm.singleobjective.geneticalgorithm.GeneticAlgorithm<S>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Algorithm<S>

    public class GeneticAlgorithm<S extends Solution<?>>
extends AbstractEvolutionaryAlgorithm<S>
    Class to perform algorithm genetic.

    This class allows you to choose between two stopping conditions to stop the execution of the algorithm. The first condition establishes a maximum number of evaluations. The second condition sets a maximum number of iterations without improving the results of the algorithm. These configurations are mutually exclusive, i.e. if you try to configure the two conditions at the same time, the last one will prevail.

    If you do not set any stopping conditions, by default the maximum number of evaluations with a value of 10000 is set. This class is a copy of GeneticAlgorithm2 but let use TournamentSelection

      • getMaxEvaluations

        public int getMaxEvaluations()
        Get the max number of evaluation.

        When the result returned by this method is 0 the stop condition of the algorithm don't take into account this value and only use the MaxNumberOfIterationWithoutImprovement GeneticAlgorithm2.getMaxNumberOfIterationWithoutImprovement(). If the value is other than 0 so it condition is taked into account.

        The default is 10000
        Returns:
        the maxEvaluations

      • setMaxEvaluations

        This disables the maximum number of iteration without improvement condition. The default is 10000

      • getMaxNumberOfIterationWithoutImprovement

        public int getMaxNumberOfIterationWithoutImprovement()
        Get the max number of iteration without a improvement of the result. When the result returned by this method is 0 the stop condition of the algorithm don't take into account this value and only use the MaxEvaluation GeneticAlgorithm2.getMaxEvaluations(). If the value is other than 0 so it condition is taked into account.

        The default is 0.
        Returns:
        MaxNumberOfIterationWithoutImprovement.
